---
to: "schema.graphql"
description: "Generate GraphQL schema with queries, mutations, and subscriptions"
category: api
requires:
  - schema_name
variables:
  schema_name: "Schema name"
  types: "Array of GraphQL type definitions"
  queries: "Array of query definitions"
  mutations: "Array of mutation definitions"
  subscriptions: "Array of subscription definitions"
  directives: "Array of custom directive definitions"
mode: overwrite



---







# {{ schema_name }} GraphQL Schema

## Directives

{% for directive in directives | default([{name: "auth", description: "Authentication directive"}]) %}
"""
{{ directive.description }}
"""
directive @{{ directive.name }}(
{% for arg in directive.args | default([]) %}
  {{ arg.name }}: {{ arg.type }}
{% endfor %}
) on {{ directive.locations | default("FIELD_DEFINITION") | join(" | ") }}

{% endfor %}

## Types

{% for type in types | default([{name: "User", fields: [{name: "id", type: "ID!"}, {name: "name", type: "String!"}]}, {name: "Post", fields: [{name: "id", type: "ID!"}, {name: "title", type: "String!"}, {name: "author", type: "User!"}])}) %}
"""
{{ type.description | default(type.name + " type") }}
"""
type {{ type.name }} {
{% for field in type.fields %}
  """
  {{ field.description | default(field.name + " field") }}
  """
  {{ field.name }}: {{ field.type }}
{% endfor %}
}

{% endfor %}

## Queries

type Query {
{% for query in queries | default([{name: "user", type: "User", description: "Get user by ID", args: [{name: "id", type: "ID!", description: "User ID"}]}, {name: "users", type: "[User!]", description: "List all users"}]) %}
  """
  {{ query.description }}
  """
  {{ query.name }}(
{% for arg in query.args | default([]) %}
    {{ arg.name }}: {{ arg.type }}
{% endfor %}
  ): {{ query.type }}
{% endfor %}
}

## Mutations

type Mutation {
{% for mutation in mutations | default([{name: "createUser", type: "User!", description: "Create new user", args: [{name: "input", type: "UserInput!", description: "User data"}]}, {name: "updateUser", type: "User!", description: "Update user", args: [{name: "id", type: "ID!"}, {name: "input", type: "UserInput!", description: "User data"}]}, {name: "deleteUser", type: "Boolean!", description: "Delete user", args: [{name: "id", type: "ID!"}]}]) %}
  """
  {{ mutation.description }}
  """
  {{ mutation.name }}(
{% for arg in mutation.args | default([]) %}
    {{ arg.name }}: {{ arg.type }}
{% endfor %}
  ): {{ mutation.type }}
{% endfor %}
}

## Subscriptions

type Subscription {
{% for subscription in subscriptions | default([{name: "userUpdated", type: "User!", description: "Subscribe to user updates", args: [{name: "id", type: "ID!", description: "User ID"}]}) %}
  """
  {{ subscription.description }}
  """
  {{ subscription.name }}(
{% for arg in subscription.args | default([]) %}
    {{ arg.name }}: {{ arg.type }}
{% endfor %}
  ): {{ subscription.type }}
{% endfor %}
}

## Input Types

{% for type in types | default([]) | selectattr("input", "true") %}
"""
Input type for {{ type.name }}
"""
input {{ type.name }}Input {
{% for field in type.fields %}
  {{ field.name }}: {{ field.type }}
{% endfor %}
}

{% endfor %}

## Signal Theory

**Signal**: `S=(linguistic, specification, inform, graphql, graphql-schema)`
- **Mode**: linguistic
- **Genre**: specification
- **Type**: inform
- **Format**: graphql
- **Structure**: graphql-schema

## Usage

```bash
# Generate GraphQL schema
unrdf template render \
  --template packages/cli/templates/api/graphql-schema.njk \
  --schema-name "MyAPI" \
  --types '[{"name": "User", "fields": [{"name": "id", "type": "ID!"}]}]'

# Validate with graphql-cli
graphql-cli validate schema.graphql

# Generate TypeScript types
graphql-codegen --schema schema.graphql --output ./src/generated/
```

## GraphQL Best Practices

1. **Use descriptive type names** - Avoid abbreviations
2. **Provide descriptions** - Document all types and fields
3. **Use non-null by default** - Add `!` to make fields required
4. **Batch queries** - Use list queries to reduce round trips
5. **Handle errors gracefully** - Use GraphQL error handling

